---
description: Generated frontend transport contracts are not hand-edited
globs: frontend/src/shared/api/contracts/**/*.ts,frontend/src/shared/realtime/generated.ts
alwaysApply: false
---

# Generated Contracts

- Treat `frontend/src/shared/api/contracts/generated.ts` and `frontend/src/shared/realtime/generated.ts` as generated code. Do not hand-edit them.
- If a generated type or realtime hub/event name is wrong or missing, fix `backend/openapi/deadmans.v1.yaml` and run `npm --prefix frontend run generate:transport` instead of patching generated output.
- Keep `frontend/src/shared/api/contracts/index.ts` focused on stable aliases and intentional re-exports; do not manually mirror the full generated surface there.
- Prefer stable aliases from `index.ts` in feature code when they provide a cleaner boundary than raw generated names.
- Partial regeneration is allowed when scoped: `generate:contracts` for HTTP schemas only, `generate:realtime` for SignalR only; use full `generate:transport` when in doubt.
